---
layout: project
title: Inclusion Tee
description: A t-shirt graphic emphasizing that you (ü) are at the center of inclusion
openGraphImage: "open graph - inclusion tee.png"
tags:
    - project
    - archive
when: 2018 (2 months)
tools: Illustrator, Photoshop
goal: Through apparel, express one’s individual responsibility for creating an inclusive environment.
---
include ../../_includes/project_utils.pug

block content
    h2 Inspiration
    .grid-3
        div
            p In 2018 I started a clothing brand called&nbsp;
                a(href="https://ntrsct.com") ntrsct
                | , which has evolved into my independent design business.
            br
            p The logomark emerged from my fascination with the numerous aspects of one’s identity and finding ways to embrace them. An X is the simplest expression of an intersection, symbolizing the point where the many elements of our identity&nbsp;meet.
            br
            p Black and white in the graphic symbolize the (illusion of) maximum contrast of our differences. While Virgil Abloh’s brand Off-White stands for the grey area between black and white, I see it differently. To me, black is&nbsp;white.
            br
            p The Inclüsion Tee was the best-selling product while running the clothing&nbsp;brand.
            br
        div
            +portfolioImg("./off-white-tag.png", "Clothing tag from Off-white", "")
        div
            +portfolioImg("./hbz-virgil-611450214-1522065262.png", "The late Virgil Abloh with his hands in prayer", "The late Virgil Abloh was the catalyst for my interest in design. One person can change your whole life. RIP Virgil Abloh (1980–2021)")
            br
    .grid-1
        +portfolioImg("./ntrsct-logo-white.png", "The ntrsct designs logo, and X with ntrsct written out horizontally", "The ntrsct designs logo")
    h1 It starts with yoü.
    .grid-2
        div
            div
                p I chose the German character, ü (u-umlaut), to symbolize the viewer (you) being the source of an inclusive environment—an ode to the reunification of East and West Germany after WWII. It also looks like a smiley face!
                br
                p This graphic resonated with me at a time when political and social issues were polarizing the American people.
                br
        div
    .grid-3
        div
            +portfolioImg("./inclusion-sketch.png", "An early sketch of the inclusion tee graphic from the Procreate app for iPad", "From sketch to reality. The figure-ground ambiguity of the X was a happy accident while working in Adobe Illustrator.")
        div
            +portfolioImg("./inclusion-white.png", "The inclusion tee graphic, spelling out inclusion with an X in the negative space", "The final graphic")
        
        div
            div.inclusion-mockup-image
                +portfolioImg("./inclusion-tee-mockup.png", "A digital mockup of the inclusion graphic in black ink on a white t-shirt", "Applied to a shirt")
    hr
    h2 Art Directed Photographs
